<section xml:id="if-else-stat"  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:lang="en-US">
    <title>If Else Statements</title>

    <xi:include href='./subgoals_evaluate_conditionals.ptx' />
    <subsection>
        <!--
        <p>
            You can watch this video or read through the content below it.
        </p>
        -->
        <p>
            Given the following declarations:
        </p>


        <program language="python">
            <input>
alpha = 2
beta = 1
delta = 3
eta = 0
gamma = 0
omega = 2.5
theta = -1.3
kappa = 3.0
mu = 0.0
rho = 0.0
            </input>
        </program>

        <p>
            Evaluate these statements and determine the value of all variables used.
        </p>


        <program language="python">
            <input>
if alpha > delta:
    eta = alpha + 2
else:
    gamma = alpha + 5
            </input>
        </program>
    </subsection>


    <subsection xml:id="subsec-ifel1">
        <title>1. Diagram which statements go together by indentation</title>

        <p>
            The first indented line (<c>eta = alpha + 2</c>) goes with the <c>if</c> statement, and the second indented line (<c>gamma = alpha + 5</c>) goes with the <c>else</c> statement.
        </p>
    </subsection>


    <subsection xml:id="subsec-ifel2">
        <title>2. For conditional, determine whether expression is true</title>

        <p>
            We evaluate <c>alpha > delta</c>, substituting <c>2</c> for <c>alpha</c> and <c>3</c> for <c>delta</c>.
        </p>

        <p>
            <c>2 > 3</c> is <c>False</c>.
        </p>
    </subsection>


    <subsection xml:id="subsec-ifel3">
        <title>3. If true, follow true branch; If false, follow next elif/else branch or exit conditional if no else branch</title>

        <p>
            The condition is <c>False</c>, so we execute the else branch.
        </p>


        <program language="python">
            <input>
gamma = alpha + 5
            </input>
        </program>

        <p>
            Substituting <c>2</c> for <c>alpha</c>, we evaluate the right-hand side to be <c>7</c> and store that in <c>gamma</c>.
            Therefore, the final value in the variables are:
        </p>

        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        <c>alpha: 2</c>
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        <c>delta: 3</c>
                    </p>
                </li>

                <li>
                    <p>
                        <c>gamma: 7</c>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
    </subsection>


    <subsection xml:id="subsec-ifel4">
        <title>4. Repeat 2 and 3 as necessary</title>

        <p>
            Repeating is not necessary in this case.
        </p>
    </subsection>
</section>
